SIMPLE: sheepish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sheepish
<hw>Sheep"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
sheep.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a sheep; bashful; over-modest; meanly or
foolishly diffident; timorous to excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wanting change of company, he will, when he comes abroad, be a
<qex>sheepish</qex> or conceited creature.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sheep"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sheep"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheepmaster</ent>⟦br⟧
